INSERT INTO book_pages (page_number, section, content, embedding, inserted_at, updated_at) VALUES (74, '2.5. Informação', 'de Johanes van der Waals e de sua equação dos gases reais, pensava-se ser permanente a condição caótica das moléculas dos gases.

## 2.5. Informação

Ciberneticamente, informação e energia se equivalem. Assim, um sistema altamente energético possui grande quantidade de informação. Na medida em que a informação é consumida o sistema marcha para a consecução de seus propósitos, sucumbindo, paralelamente, à entropia. Se o sistema for aberto, ele poderá receber informação do universo exterior, fazendo baixar a entropia, ou, ao menos, mantendo constante a relação energia/entropia, que lhe define o potencial. A entropia, como vimos, reflete uma tendência da natureza, que é a de degradar a energia, fazendo com que as coisas se acomodem nos seus respectivos lugares, quando, então, cessará todo o movimento,¹³ isto é, o sistema perecerá, por exaustão da energia.

---

13. *Os brâmanes acreditam que em um futuro remoto ocorrerá a parada do universo no "ponto morto", durante a "noite de Brama", em decorrência da degradação da energia, por eles inferida, com grande sabedoria, há quase três mil anos, no Livro dos Vedas.*', '[-0.023973588,0.03341548,-0.03738378,0.021291269,-0.005482324,0.043770127,0.05818548,0.06810481,0.032010507,0.09060233,0.02526817,-0.024862023,0.011090908,-0.029638045,-0.02962464,-0.0456643,0.050582968,0.057946768,-0.0050064973,0.031914055,0.20115298,0.0038587537,0.00093777874,0.03163116,-0.071617,0.07201249,-0.06985909,0.033291746,0.0017093403,-0.048611004,-0.026556997,0.028940015,0.07885376,-0.02266465,0.003430681,-0.0237488,0.03527742,-0.04646572,-0.040107585,0.04040771,-0.05792591,-0.0053923493,-0.04010201,-0.01697718,-0.0072244257,0.017924728,0.025879247,-0.019378755,-0.0505922,-0.013673875,-0.05275734,-0.04454253,-0.032438792,-0.018383112,-0.016913677,-0.0615882,-0.042625405,-0.057547003,-0.030107502,-0.07452461,0.04073597,0.027338644,-0.012357016,0.03588314,0.030662429,0.01410008,-0.008954409,0.032952916,0.022798548,-0.0062936223,0.017636778,-0.011985326,0.019099593,0.006451232,-0.041376736,0.07169171,-0.0006213755,0.024954727,-3.634722e-05,-0.10176466,0.08985828,0.0563829,0.011548072,-0.06005854,0.01344973,0.0005588093,0.0078079235,0.03081958,0.037953272,-0.039826885,-0.055503372,-0.019746266,-0.00017247665,-0.048411682,0.058537427,0.022053203,-0.01246417,-0.047209386,0.08830381,-0.06972715,0.041861832,0.05489164,-0.0045024576,0.019795874,-0.06291752,-0.04677645,-0.003993142,0.0023840123,0.053594604,0.12990665,-0.06866541,-0.019510433,-0.096703045,-0.07729134,-0.0016682076,-0.017053876,-0.03860457,-0.006164628,0.036398258,0.014894782,-0.023664659,-0.07237273,0.022875907,-0.053192925,0.089406244,-0.02716271,0.052728627,7.4857435e-33,-0.08802464,-0.048020884,0.004925374,-0.003275051,-0.012478681,0.05507997,-0.061094992,-0.030895023,0.07048287,0.044627428,-0.07665699,0.18932661,0.0026129736,0.030944055,0.046