INSERT INTO book_pages (page_number, section, content, embedding, inserted_at, updated_at) VALUES (169, 'Página 169', 'A robotização do homem jamais ocorrerá, por maior que seja a autonomia da empresa, o automatismo de suas máquinas e de seus mecanismos de feedback, e a automação de seus bens de produção.

Por outro lado, não há razão lógica para se pensar que somente a máquina é totalmente determinada, e que a instabilidade do homem, quanto aos seus desígnios, é um razão a mais para que se lhe cerceie, ao máximo, a autonomia, ao longo das hierarquias de controle.

Injusta "capitis diminutio" para o espírito humano! É verdade que a máquina (e especificamente como sistema mecânico), mercê do mecanismo de auto-regulação por feedback, é perfeitamente determinada, mas o grau de incerteza do homem somente é elevado quando as variáveis de seu comportamento emanam do livre arbítrio, isto é, do direito, que lhe é assegurado, de decidir a respeito de seu próprio destino. O "Homo faber", como um fator de produção, é perfeitamente determ

---

*(continuação da pág. anterior) Resposta de Reuter, imperturbável:*
*— É verdade. E você, já pensou para que vai vender seus carros?"...*', '[-0.0035299333,0.045459785,-0.014412215,-0.042340405,-0.011110438,-0.004269395,0.065855876,0.09998744,-0.060845103,0.0971517,0.082286306,-0.027379042,0.032972675,0.015880322,-0.052208677,-0.0061989143,-0.022073269,0.04682806,-0.024600249,0.10454173,0.06799518,0.02546112,-0.015065895,0.0996226,-0.13591412,0.010793114,0.009662017,0.02031656,-0.08268386,-0.08400528,-0.05052092,0.0022342498,0.15519406,-0.06677436,-0.025418954,0.017344546,0.030581094,-0.02540042,-0.012533075,0.04360721,-0.0016830745,-0.09263647,-0.025362924,-0.056624,0.04202726,0.052286513,0.054563046,0.01853391,0.054061852,-0.038465478,-0.0959169,-0.0014525695,0.008065146,-0.010646673,-0.023622459,-0.022502549,-0.031217732,0.007653429,0.03583273,-0.040426273,0.027043963,0.005183913,0.027785033,0.061558574,0.07630199,0.005020135,-0.054087654,-0.028428573,-0.023619786,0.079363815,0.06363096,-0.10921037,-0.021262502,-0.012485895,0.020748883,0.06767732,-0.102679305,-0.0040567885,0.07882783,-0.0131583875,-0.011152387,-0.039078835,-0.0098135285,0.005339266,-0.043615244,0.007321478,-0.034261677,-0.021258572,0.06112266,-0.0012331213,-0.0036865037,-0.00090214337,-0.10933634,-0.050961893,-0.0038483874,-0.021201061,0.019703351,-0.08723683,0.1117345,0.00248879,0.010544107,0.010992651,-0.043419477,0.009634632,0.03082134,0.02630242,-0.019062037,-0.054074783,-0.020367187,0.07264326,-0.07073464,-0.058638927,-0.07241621,-0.033561826,0.039823037,0.038882367,0.005521548,-0.034944117,0.017818807,-0.0641559,0.020186383,-0.120727375,0.03918115,-0.08930809,0.11283747,0.0034676227,0.014731477,8.725979e-33,-0.076225035,-0.02609919,-0.010696056,-0.03570903,-0.021619935,-0.005892843,-0.058805943,0.053803455,0.067661844,0.012363559,-0.053652324,0.058323514,0.009856911,0.044814687,0.08515498,-0.029108642,0.05674682,-0.06143956,-0.032270756,-0.008625633,-0.0049183415,0.036698047,0.01640905,-0.011279287,0.003472423,0.0480707,-0.0023533648,-0.030645214,-0.0457106