INSERT INTO book_pages (page_number, section, content, embedding, inserted_at, updated_at) VALUES (227, 'Página 227', 'do, abrigar o produto final do raciocínio. Mas, inexistindo a causa primeira...?

A geração espontânea do conhecimento, espécie de partenogênese mental, sempre preocupou os gregos. Platão resolve a questão, com sua teoria sobre a imortalidade da alma, afirmando que todo conhecimento é reminiscência, ao dizer, com Sócrates, no MENON, que "não há ensino, mas recordação". Assim, o começo está no próprio homem, o argumento dedutivo fica por conta da maiêutica, ou parturição das idéias. Aristóteles, mais uma vez, põe-se contra seu mestre e denuncia-lhe a epistemologia ao questionar a existência do conhecimento a priori, inato. Para ele todo conhecimento tem origem nos sentidos, que vão imprimindo, na "tabula rasa" que é o espírito humano na alvorada da vida, os relatos das experiências acumuladas que lhe servirão de substrato intelectual. Com Aristóteles a indução, como método de raciocínio, adquire a importância que, até hoje, conserva na Lógica Material. Mas, ao negar a existência do conhecimento a priori, Aristóteles deixa mais uma vez sem resposta aquela questão crucial: e o ponto de', '[0.02451999,0.018533507,-0.0043184445,-0.04505119,-0.009839132,-0.0025587203,0.043938246,0.07464616,0.0024968854,0.12030092,-0.0007894122,-0.019030387,-0.00035347423,0.025095435,-0.040348068,0.009631633,-0.026559824,0.009201169,-0.0010373034,0.11963342,0.09702007,-0.009135016,-0.016779527,0.08334445,-0.081870936,0.017925302,0.006874943,0.020113343,-0.076609135,0.008736229,-0.018226521,0.039453242,0.094700426,-0.016181082,0.027934445,0.025993604,0.0067106755,-0.010203222,0.0029478485,0.008843755,-0.0013133072,0.04233083,-0.048617173,0.021063363,-0.01011869,-0.023562225,0.10244866,0.07705681,0.016324306,-0.021977969,-0.09980225,0.031838182,-0.07519799,-0.017443644,-0.050447028,-0.025574652,-0.009303049,-0.046629213,-0.0118305525,-0.016092205,-0.06364558,-0.00050579215,0.018171359,0.044876195,0.059189614,0.034262802,0.005278678,0.003948746,-0.047328122,0.05650299,0.059194583,-0.002809907,0.04574914,0.031577647,-0.020529307,0.06741459,-0.001872458,0.061359957,-0.033360