INSERT INTO book_pages (page_number, section, content, embedding, inserted_at, updated_at) VALUES (250, 'Página 250', 'qual se diz que os feedback corretivos de erros são necessàriamente negativos. Em contrapartida, quando f(t). f(T) é menor do que 1, tornando positiva a função global de transferência (feedback positivo), esta será maior que a função de transferência da rede principal, e o efeito será contrário: o erro será ampliado com relação ao sinal.

Para encerrar, façamos uma aplicação numérica da g(t) para a função de demanda Y = 160 X – 16 X² com que iniciamos o último exemplo de feedback. O diagrama de efeitos imediatos será:

> **[Figura — Diagrama de efeitos imediatos com dois blocos: bloco superior da rede principal Y = 160X–16X² com entrada E=i+Of(T) (i=8/2) e saída O=400; bloco inferior da rede de feedback com X = ±√(25.600–64Y)/32, saída O=256; Of(T)=3]**

Observe-se que para uma saída O = 400 a f(T) será igual a zero, mantendo-se a entrada original, que é correta. Nesse caso o feedback é nulo por não ter o que corrigir.', '[-0.010226295,0.00888842,-0.037338134,-0.053244974,-0.047450695,-0.023082448,-0.0050245244,0.12637497,0.047204364,0.030289132,0.046666484,-0.033085886,0.036647335,-0.02640781,-0.0047047846,0.033426076,0.09866613,0.0579077,-0.07558816,0.045429666,0.14764759,-0.1033663,-0.08601534,0.0020954846,-0.14600866,-0.028872222,-0.09967482,0.025351403,-0.0412767,-0.14071645,-0.084530585,0.028481394,0.07587817,-0.051489387,-0.08294062,-0.02324303,-0.016696367,-0.07147774,-0.046978798,0.022612467,-0.043717396,0.049087577,0.017277652,-0.072492994,-0.00590502,-0.011614509,0.007257126,0.05804101,-0.02976922,-0.041574493,0.013973225,0.011865656,-0.028328193,0.020231828,0.031349562,-0.03922231,0.06273249,-0.024395144,0.00654009,-0.03237039,0.026531385,-0.008067879,-0.018028934,0.010399581,0.05902469,-0.028346704,-0.026932592,-0.029900344,-0.09515042,0.030626394,0.033823814,-0.09639957,-0.023561586,-0.038989313,0.09573428,0.044607606,-0.017531637,0.13782723,-0.035056155,-0.04426906,0.07635733,0.006392768,-0.053485602,-0.079698004,0.012347739,-0.03520249,-0.0125463735,0.038900226,0.038639117,0.039989464,0.020620668,0.08521824,-0.12736742,0.011136691,0.02336648,-0.011975618,0.030663293,-0.031388275,0.05797985,0.032262456,0.098047346,0.022024253,0.013466795,0.027132004,-0.057277877,-0.041041035,0.027650293,0.05699751,0.017901538,0.023045653,-0.124698184,-0.03991495,-0.031750526,-0.038769614,0.007253117,-0.04648024,-0.011819044,-0.04072378,-0.0464963,-0.037058506,0.092011206,-0.11310616,-0.040930554,-0.0014651185,0.014209357,-0.03477131,-0.021199033,1.1477523e-32,-0.03324344,0.008094221,-0.030839542,-0.064778864,-0.027138557,0.01213348,-0.044448778,-0.0052538845,0.055709727,-0.0096006,-0.12554416,0.03264753,-0.009811629,0.037750807,0.023052404,-0.031337164,0.07750689,-0.038384117,0.019693108,-0.026739405,-0.0018264123,0.0